                            <h4>The vegetable products in the province of Taza.</h4>
                            </div>
                        <p>Vegetable products are among the vibrant artisanal activities of the province of Taza, particularly in rural areas with significant vegetation cover of palm and vegetable hair. Manufactured products diversify in terms of their shape or the use of raw materials; there are articles made of palm and others from vegetable hair.</p>
                            <div class="destination-details-image">
                                <a href="destination.html"><img src="/images/Taza_Artisanat.jpg" alt="image"></a>
                            </div>

                            <div class="destination-common-title">
                                <h4>More Details</h4>
                            </div>
                        <p>The rural municipality of Beni Frassen, located 60km northwest of the city of Taza in the province, is considered the main stronghold of vegetable production for several reasons. The most significant one is the historical attachment of the population in this municipality to this heritage across generations. Besides, the mountainous nature of the region has encouraged its inhabitants to engage in this activity due to their proximity to the sources of raw materials and to increase their income, as the yield from agricultural activities, their primary source of livelihood, is low.</p>
                            <div class="dd-image-container">
